    "created_at": "2018-06-20T18:30:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-06-20T18:30:20Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@andre2007 while the core is unlikely to switch to betterC soon, it may be an interesting exercise to wrap core with an idiomatic betterC API or a full D api. \r\nSomething like that can be done out of repo with a view to migrate into grpc-ecosystem if you are interested.\r\nSome points that might be useful to consider if you go down that path.\r\n1) Wrapping core - we do a 6 weekly release cycle, so be sure that you can wrap the latest version of core and it can be a moving target.\r\n2) We have interop tests that you can use to test how your server / client interops in many cases with other gRPC implementations\r\n3) Test suite.. it would be good to look at some wrapped language test suite and give similar coverage. "
  },
